title.narrative: 401 STRENGTHENING PREVENTIVE AND RESPONSIVE CP SYSTEMS

description.narrative: By 2022, child protection systems and structures have adequate human and financial resources, institutional capacity, monitoring and data management ability in selected states to deliver preventive and responsive child protection service, which contributes to Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

description.narrative: UNICEF supported governments in 17 states to strengthen child protection workforce for improved prevention and response services to 350,500 vulnerable children. In 10 states, UNICEF strengthened capacities of responders for providing healing and recovery services to 33,189 child survivors of violence and abuse. 133,370 children received psychosocial care through UNICEF supported safe spaces in three states during emergencies. 1,023 Special Courts for trial of child sexual abuse cases were supported through advocacy, design and capacity development by UNICEF. Partnership with Supreme Court and High Courts supported the acceleration of child care reform and the strengthening of standards of alternative care | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2020
